<title type="html"><![CDATA[specifying MMC3 earlier vs later revisions IRQ differences ?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8775&amp;p=92001#p92001"><![CDATA[
Right now, there isn't, so which MMC3 irq behavior is emulated is up to the emulator.<br /><br />At some point, the newer MMC3 behavior (IRQ fires when the counter is <em>equal</em> to 0, instead of only when it <em>reaches</em> 0) was considered the "normal" behavior, so I'm kinda surprised to see the older behavior being implemented.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=21">Drag</a> — Sat Mar 31, 2012 12:02 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
